title: For Sale/Trade:  Mauser Chileno Modelo 1895 7 x 57 mag
postcontent: WTT or Sale my Mauser Chileno Modelo 1895 7 x 57 mag with 22 rounds of Peters Rustless 7MM Mauser 175 grain soft point bullets. Bullets are almost as old as the gun but I have shot 20 rounds through it and it shoots fantastic. As you can see the gun has been what some people call sporterised. Basically it’s given a smaller stock causing it to jump from its past weight on 9.5 lbs to 7.8 lbs. That makes it much easier to carry through the woods. It was made in Loewe Berlin Germany and the S/N is E746 which makes this an Antique (any Mauser with a S/N between A-K are considered antique). S/N’s match on the receiver, bolt and trigger mechanism. It does have the O with the X in it on the butt cap and trigger mechanism and on the barrel telling me this was an artillery rifle and all parts are original except the wood. It has a very clean and clear Chileno Army emblem stamped on the barrel as you would expect. The bluing is outstanding 90%. Nice piece to add to anyone’s collection.

title: For Sale:  Remington 870 Express 20 gauge magnum; home defender w/ lots of ammo!
postcontent:
This package deal comes with 700 rounds of ammo!!!  What a deal!

Since I am having a hard time selling my ceramics on time to pay rent, I am forced to sell my favorite home defender.  It is a Remington 870 Express in 20 gauge magnum.  (Of course, it will take any 20 gauge shell regardless of length.)

It features a Knoxx Blackhawk recoil-reducing, adjustable length of pull stock with a pistol grip.  It is a very comfortable firearm no matter what your build is.  It has an 18.5 inch barrel, with a magazine extension that ends flush with the muzzle.  The barrel is a smooth bore with cylinder choke.  (I think that means no choke, or perhaps minimal choke.)

It will hold 5 + 1 with 2 3/4" shells or shorter, and will hold 4 + 1 with magnum shells.

Also included is LOTS of ammo, a soft case for storage or transport, and 121 empty shells for reloading.

Ammo includes: A box of 5 magnum (3") slugs; 26 2 3/4" slugs; 15 rounds of #3 buckshot; plus another 653 rounds of bird shot.  Most of the bird shot is #8 or #7 1/2 shot, but there are also a few boxes of #6; several rounds of #5; and a few boxes of #4 shot.

All total there are around 700 rounds of ammunition!  (+ / - a few for counting error.)

The shotgun functions flawlessly, and is the PERFECT weapon for home defense for ANY man or woman with a lighter frame, such as me.  Yes, a 12 gauge packs more punch, but also has MUCH more recoil.  This 20 gauge looks menacing, will stop anyone, and is a true joy to shoot.  Anyone could shoot this shotgun all day long and not have a sore shoulder.  (Just don't forget the hearing protection.)  Try doing that with a 12 gauge.

If you need a home defender now and can't find ammo for anything else, this is the tool for you!  This is perfect to have in the house for the wife or teenager, or even the man of the house.

Asking $600 for all, I will not break up firearm and ammo, so please don't ask.  

Call or text me today.  If this doesn't sell by the time I pay rent, I will take down the listing as I DON'T want to sell.  316 - seven 3 four - 5 zero 31   Please, no e-mails, as I don't have internet at the house and only check it once or twice a day.
